    "content": "SAM9X60-EK Evaluation Board . | Setup the SD card . | Download harmony MPU bootstrap loader from this location | Copy the downloaded boot loader binary (boot.bin) and generated application binary (harmony.bin)into the SD card | Insert the SD card into the SDMMC connector J4 on the board | . | Connect the USB port J22 on board to the computer using a micro USB cable (to enable debug com port) | Jumpers J20, J21 and J13 must be open. | Jumper J2 and J3 must be shorted. | Use USB Micro B connector (J7) on the board to connect the USB Device to the USB Host PC. | LED D1 indicates USB Device Configuration Set Complete event (the USB device functionality has been activated by the USB Host). | Press the switch SW1 to trigger communication from the USB Device to the USB Host. Note: Reset push button on SAM9X60 EK is labeled as SW3 . | . ",
